    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>Judson treats cyclic groups in a separate chapter (Ch. 4) and proves the fundamental theorem of cyclic groups: every subgroup of Z_n is of the form Z_(n/d) for a divisor d of n. We compress this into the lattice diagram. The one-step subgroup test (a * b inverse in H) is equivalent to the two-step test but more elegant. The order-divides-group-order fact is a preview of Lagrange's theorem in Ch. 5.</p>

